			<header>
				<h1>Careers</h1>
									<h2>We are currently seeking a Head of Marketing and a Social Media Content Creator to join our team.</h2>
							</header>
		</div>
	</div>
		<div class="row">
				<div class="col-xs-12 col-m-8 post">
									<article>
									<p>Founded in 2017, Hello Neighbor works to improve the lives of refugee and immigrant families by matching them with dedicated neighbors to guide and support them in their new lives. In that time, <strong style="color:#ff6c36">we’ve supported over 800 people</strong> from <strong style="color:#6ec829">17 countries of origin</strong> through local and national programs. We are continuously growing and looking for new ways to provide the best support to our newest neighbors. <strong style="color: #57c9e8">It’s a great time to join Hello Neighbor!</strong></p>

<p><a href="https://www.helloneighbor.io/get-involved">Read more about our mission, vision and core values.</a></p>

<h2>Why It’s Great to Work Here:</h2>

<ul>
<li>We are doing innovative work supporting refugees and immigrants</li>
<li>We are building a diverse and multicultural community and workplace</li>
<li>You will learn a lot and develop new skills</li>
<li>We like to take big risks</li>
<li>You opinion matters and will help shape Hello Neighbor’s growth and impact</li>
<li>We are a small collaborative team that works together closely</li>
<li>We are one-part startup and one-part nonprofit, you’ll get to learn about both</li>
<li>We are gaining recognition on a national scale and it’s an exciting time to join our team</li>
<li>We have a hybrid work model with flexibility to work remotely on Monday and Friday and from our sunny and inviting office in the East End Tuesday-Thursday</li>
</ul>

<blockquote>
  <p>“I’ve had so many opportunities to grow within and alongside Hello Neighbor. There is a strong culture of peer learning and problem solving and one that values people and their contributions at every level.” <br><strong>- Rachel Vinciguerra, Assistant Director of National Programs</strong></p>
</blockquote>

<h2>Our Benefits:</h2>
<p>At Hello Neighbor, we believe a happy, healthy, well-balanced person makes an even better team member and employee. We offer comprehensive benefits that not only help you build your career but support a full and healthy lifestyle.</p>
<h3>Hello Neighbor is proud to offer:</h3>

<ul>
<li><em>Competitive salaries</em></li>
<li><em>Medical insurance for you, your spouse or domestic partner and dependents</em></li>
<li><em>401(k) savings plan with employer matching program</em></li>
<li><em>10 days of PTO per year, in addition to holiday office closures</em></li>
<li><em>3 paid floating holidays to be used at your discretion</em></li>
<li><em>3 paid sick or personal days</em></li>
<li><em>1 paid day annually for community service</em></li>
<li><em>Unlimited paid time off for civic engagement</em></li>
<li><em>Annual office closure the last week of December</em></li>
</ul>

<div style="background-color: #fedd3d; padding: .75em; display: inline-block"><p style="margin: 0">We require COVID-19 vaccination and a booster for full-time employees.</p></div>
                                      
<hr style="margin: 3em auto -1em auto">

<h2>Current Openings</h2>

<p>See a list of our current job openings below and click or scroll for more details about each position.</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="#head-of-marketing">Head Of Marketing</a></li>
<li><a href="#social-media-content-creator">Social Media Content Creator</a></li>
</ul>

<hr>

<div style="background-color: #ededed; border-radius: 8px; padding: 2em 2em .2em 2em; margin: 0; text-align: left">                                                                            

<a name="head-of-marketing" style="text-decoration: none">
<h2 style="color:#022169; margin: 0 0 1em 0"> Head Of Marketing (Full-Time)</h2>
</a>

<p><strong>Hello Neighbor is seeking an experienced Head of Marketing to join our growing team!</strong> 2022 marks our 5th year of operation and our first with a $1 million budget. We have an ambitious year of anniversary activations planned and are excited to post this newly created position to join the team and hit the ground running.</p>

<div class="accordion">
        <div class="accordion-head">
            <a data-dropdown-target="#head-of-marketing-details" href="#">
              <h3 style="color: #022169; text-decoration: underline"><b>Details</b></h3>            
            </a>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-body collapse" id="head-of-marketing-details">
            <p><strong>Reports To:</strong> Founder and Executive Director<br>
            <strong>Oversees:</strong> Two direct reports plus additional contractors</p>

            <h3>Key Responsibilities</h3>

            <ul>
                <li>Leads development of Marketing Communications Plan and ensures adherence to the goals and brand outlined therein.</li>
                <li>Leads all marketing campaign activities laddering up to annual fundraising goals.</li>
                <li>Leads donor segmentation and strategy with the development team.</li>
                <li>Responsible for the achievement of the goals and objectives of the Marketing Communications Plan. Ensure that evaluation systems are in place related to these goals and objectives and report progress to Hello Neighbor’s Leadership Team.</li>
                <li>Ensure that the appropriate systems, staffing and procedures are in place to properly and reasonably support marketing and communications.</li>
                <li>Works closely with program staff to design and implement communications strategies and effective messaging for organizational and project-specific goals.</li>
                <li>Work with the CEO, Leadership Team and Accounting Manager to develop annual budgets for marketing and communications, and monitor progress, assure adherence and evaluate performance.</li>
                <li>Assists staff in ensuring our communications are culturally competent and reach diverse audiences.</li>
                <li>Manages some partnerships that support organizational marketing and fundraising goals.</li>
                <li>Ensure that brand identity, messaging and marketing and communications strategy are infused in all organizational efforts (programming, development, network support).</li>
                <li>Develop, track, and implement metrics and reporting structures across all campaigns.</li>
            </ul>

                <h3>About You:</h3>

            <ul>
                <li>Deep respect and understanding for the privacy of the individuals we serve, while being an avid supporter of the work we do.</li>
                <li>Avid and passionate marketer that is interested in getting into the weeds, while also leading strategy.</li>
                <li>Strong visual aesthetic and understanding of brand development.</li>
                <li>Metrics and ROI-based approach to planning.</li>
                <li>5-7 years of experience leading marketing organizations.</li>
            </ul>

                <h3>Details/Benefits:</h3>

            <ul>
                <li>Estimated start date: June 1st</li>
                <li>Salary range: $60,000-65,000</li>
            </ul>

                <h3>To Apply:</h3>

            <ul>
                <li>We are accepting applications on a rolling basis until April 30th. Selected candidates will be invited to interview in April and May.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
</div>  


<p><a class="typeform-share button" href="https://helloneighbor.typeform.com/to/An6EDqxu" data-mode="drawer_right" style="margin: 1em 0 0 0; display:inline-block; text-decoration:none;background-color:#DE3013;color:white;cursor:pointer; font-weight: 700; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", "Roboto", "Oxygen", "Ubuntu", "Cantarell", "Fira Sans", "Droid Sans", "Helvetica Neue", sans-serif;font-size:1em;line-height:1em;text-align:center; border:none; padding:1em; border-radius:4px;max-width:100%;white-space:nowrap;overflow:hidden;text-overflow:ellipsis;font-weight:bold;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-moz-osx-font-smoothing:grayscale;" data-submit-close-delay="5" target="_blank">Apply </a> <script> (function() { var qs,js,q,s,d=document, gi=d.getElementById, ce=d.createElement, gt=d.getElementsByTagName, id="typef_orm_share", b="https://embed.typeform.com/"; if(!gi.call(d,id)){ js=ce.call(d,"script"); js.id=id; js.src=b+"embed.js"; q=gt.call(d,"script")[0]; q.parentNode.insertBefore(js,q) } })() </script>
