<h2>Important Notes:</h2>

<ul>
<li>Hello Neighbor has placed COVID procedures and social distancing policies in place for the safety of all staff, volunteers, and families.</li>
<li>Hello Neighbor stands with the Black community in Pittsburgh and throughout the world. We are committed to being an anti-racist and inclusive organization. Read about <a href="https://www.helloneighbor.io/black-lives-matter">our commitment</a> and our <a href="https://www.helloneighbor.io/about/what-we-do">Core Values</a>.</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>Equal Opportunity Employer</h2>

<p>At Hello Neighbor, we are committed to being an inclusive workplace where diversity in all its forms is championed. Hello Neighbor is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity or Veteran status. We also consider qualified applicants with criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. If you require special accommodation, please let us know.</p>

<p><em>Data shows that women more frequently do not apply to a job because they don’t feel that they meet all of the qualifications listed. Our job descriptions are general overviews, not a mandatory comprehensive list.  If you feel passionate about our efforts and believe that you have the skills to contribute to the growth of our organization, we want to hear from you!</em></p>

